      <!-- 6 · INCUBATION -->
      <section id="incubation">
        <h2 class="cag-h2">How do you hatch a fertile African Grey egg? (Essential incubation metrics)</h2>
        <p>Hatching a Psittacus erithacus egg is demanding, precise work, and we'd rather you walk in clear-eyed: it means holding a steady 99.5°F and managed humidity for 28–30 days, turning several times a day, then hand-feeding a helpless chick around the clock. We publish the real incubation temperature, humidity and turning numbers below because every fake farm promises a PDF and none of them tell you the truth.</p>
