        <h3 class="cag-h3">The 28–30 day reality — incubation day by developmental milestone</h3>
        <p>From set to pip runs about 28–30 days for an African Grey, with hatching itself unfolding over roughly 24–72 hours once the chick breaks through. Those are biological windows, not delivery estimates, and rushing or "helping" a hatch is a common way to lose a chick that would have made it — here is what each stage looks like on the candling light.</p>
        <div class="otA" role="group" aria-label="Incubation day versus developmental milestone">
