        <h4 class="cag-h4">What arrival day looks like</h4>
        <p>Arrival day is a rest-and-settle day, not an incubate-immediately scramble: we tell buyers to let shipped eggs sit pointed-end-up at room temperature for several hours so the air cell restabilizes before setting. That single instruction — which the fake farms never send — protects the clutch you paid for.</p>

